President Muhammadu Buhari last night hosted all the aspirants for All Progressives Congress(APC) national chairmanship to a dinner at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The aspirants are Abdullahi Adamu (Nasarawa), Tanko Al’Makura (Nasarawa State), George Akume (Benue State), Abdul-laziz  Yari,  (Niger State), Saliu Mustapha (Kwara), Mohammed Sani-Musa (Niger), and Muhammed Eksu(Niger).   2023: Bode George, Oladipo, 35 others to determine PDP…     IMF ready to lend more to Nigeria     Soyinka decries protest over OAU VC   The dinner ended  Buhari’s phased interactions with critical stakeholders of the ruling party, having met earlier in the day with Progressive Governors Forum (PGF) members and some of the party’s stakeholders. Although details of the closed-doors engagement were not available as of press time,  sources hinted that it was a  part of last minutes’ efforts at closing the ranks within the APC  ahead of its national convention on Saturday. The Chairman, Caretaker and Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee of the party and Governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni;  Chief of Staff to the President, Prof. Ibrahim Gambari, and Secretary to the Government of the Federation,  Boss Mustapha, also attended the meeting Buhari had with the chairmanship aspirants.